[[File:Old_Hartford_before_the_flood_2014-07-10_05-35.jpg|thumbnail|Old Hartford before the flood]]

'''Hartford''' is an [[unincorporated community]] in [[Union Township, Ohio County, Indiana|Union Township]], [[Ohio County, Indiana|Ohio County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]].<ref>{{cite gnis|435824|Hartford, Ohio County, Indiana|2016-08-29}}</ref>

==History==
Hartford was laid out about 1817.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b040AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA476#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=History of Dearborn and Ohio Counties, Indiana | publisher=F. E. Weakley | year=1885 | pages=476}}</ref> In its peak years, Hartford was a point on the stagecoach route from Madison to Aurora.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Best Books on|author2=Federal Writers' Project|title=Indiana: A Guide to the Hoosier State|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2r22OGS6yeAC&pg=PA375|year=1941|publisher=Best Books on|isbn=978-1-62376-013-7|page=375}}</ref> Before the flood of 1937 there were four mills, and a general store which opened up in 1978 and closed in the mid-1980s.

A post office was established at Hartford in 1844, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1891.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.postalhistory.com/postoffices.asp?task=display&state=IN&county=Ohio | title=Ohio County | publisher=Jim Forte Postal History | accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref>

==Geography==
Hartford is located at {{coord|38|59|35|N|84|57|25|W|type:city}}. Laughtery Creek lies to the north of the community.

